name: Bump in the Night
overview: Bump in the Night is an animated series by Danger Productions that was filmed using stop-motion animation and aired on ABC from 1994 to 1995. It was created and directed by Ken Pontac and David Bleiman. The series was then broadcast on Toon Disney from 1998 to 2001.

episodes.name: Made in Japan, Dr Coddle M.D.
episodes.overview:
Made in Japan:  Bumpy mails in a cereal box top for a free Turbo-Totro-Noid. A cute little robot arrives, disappointing Bumpy. But, Bumpy is soon to learn that this robot can grow and become a huge, kinda scary robot.  The robot eventually gets Squishy to help him get back to his family in Osaka.

Dr. Coddle M.D:  Molly orders medical instruction books from the Easy-Does-It Doctor Correspondence Course. Bumpy accidently eats the books and replaces them with home improvement manuals.

episodes.overview:

episodes.name: I dream of silverfish, Story problems
episodes.overview:
I DREAM OF SILVERFISH - Bumpy and Squishy find a "genie" in a lamp. (Really it's just a bug named Phil Silverfish.) The genie requires relaxation before he can start granting wishes.

STORY PROBLEMS - Bumpy eats The Boy's homework, and then tries to redo it. It's tough going, but the answer was inside Mr. Bumpy all along.

episodes.overview:

ALL YOU NEED IS GLOVE - Bumpy fights with a glove for a perfect left-foot sock.

episodes.name: Long Long Day/Destructo's Flipside
episodes.overview:
LONG LONG DAY - Musical skit, set up by Destructo and the Closet Monster fighting over possesion of Mr. Bumpy.

DESTRUCTO'S FLIPSIDE - Bumpy puts Destructo's battery in backwards. This reverses Destructo's ego, bringing out his gentle side.

episodes.name: Love Stinks/Love's Labor Bumped
episodes.overview:
LOVE STINKS - Molly falls into a trashcan and attracts the affections of a stinkbug named Odiferous J. Stench.

LOVE'S LABOR BUMPED - Destructo has a crush on Molly. Bumpy dresses up like Molly (sort of) and teases Destructo

episodes.name: It Sang from Beyond the Stars/Journey to the Center of the Lungfish
episodes.overview:
IT SANG FROM BEYOND THE STARS - Musical skit starring Gloog and Sleemoth as musical invaders.

JOURNEY TO THE CENTER OF THE LUNGFISH - Bumpy, Squishington, and Molly are swallowed by a lungfish. Inside, they meet Captain Jetlag (a silverfish) who tries to help them sail out of the fish.

BUMPY THE UNTRAPPABLE - The boy tries to catch Bumpy with traps.

episodes.name: It Came from the Closet
episodes.overview: IT CAME FROM THE CLOSET - In an attempt to quickly clean his closet, the boy pushes the Closet Monster under the bed, unfortunately for Mr. Bumpy.

episodes.name: Comfort Schmumfort
episodes.overview: COMFORT SCHMUMFORT - Space aliens abduct Bumpy and Squish, leaving "harmless" Molly behind.

episodes.name: Bump and Roll

episodes.name: I Got Needs/Beauty and the Bump
episodes.overview:
I GOT NEEDS - Starts with invading Vikings and turns into musical number for Bumpy as they try to make him their leader.

BEAUTY AND THE BUMP - Bumpy falls for an antique china doll under glass, who becomes the Princess in his fairy-tale dream.

episodes.name: When the Music Starts
episodes.overview: WHEN THE MUSIC STARTS -Mr. Bumpy and Molly try to convince Squishington to play in their band.

episodes.name: Neat and Clean/Nothing But the Tooth
episodes.overview:
NEAT AND CLEAN - Begins as Adventures in Microbia, then breaks into a song with Squishy, Molly, Destructo, Bumpy, Cute Dolls.

NOTHING BUT THE TOOTH - Bumpy's teeth turn on him when Squishington accidentally pulls them out trying to fix a sore tooth.

episodes.name: Water Way to Go/Cold Turkey
episodes.overview:
WATER WAY TO GO - Squishington withers and drys up when the plumber turns off the water.

COLD TURKEY - A frozen turkey comes to life and escapes from the freezer
